    "en": {
      "title": "Not all filling stations can supply fuel on a daily basis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Due to inability to meet the daily fuel demand, Q.R. Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, Minister of Electricity and Energy, says that the system was introduced and due to the foreign exchange crisis, the import of fuel will have to be restricted in the next 12 months.",
        "The Minister says that the Petroleum Corporation has not distributed fuel to every petrol station on a daily basis and it is practically impossible to supply fuel to every petrol station even if the stocks are unlimited."
      ],
